comments.body:
Please update the version in the _index.d.ts_ file, apparently this is version [3.43.3](https://developers.google.com/maps/documentation/javascript/releases#3.43.3).

>   *   Renamed the `google.maps.MouseEvent` interface to `google.maps.MapMouseEvent` and added a `domEvent` property, providing direct access to the underlying event from the DOM.

The documentation says that this version should not have a patch version, as the build process adds that.  This is probably why the CI failed?  If I get time I'll create an account and login to see the specific reason(s).
This is the only way I know how to use a global type whose name is the same as the name from the local namespace.
